title: Study Day: A History of Gardens in 10 Objects
desc: Be inspired by the rich horticultural heritage of our surroundings on this study day with garden historians Davis Marsh and Letta Jones. The Palace?s gardens became famous under Bishop Compton (1675-1713), known as the Botanising Bishop, who imported many seeds and cuttings from all over the world to cultivate at Fulham. Discover in an interactive way the botanical, cultural and artistic diversity of the subject.
